public class NumericFilenameGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
implements NameGenerator

A NameGenerator to use with FilenameGenerator for generating a padded numeric sequence of filenames.

Constructor Detail

NumericFilenameGenerator

public NumericFilenameGenerator(java.lang.String ext,
                                int startNum,
                                int keyLen)
Construct a default instance.

Generated filenames will be of the form of keyLen zero padded digits with a decimal number and the given extension appended; starting with the (padded) startNum.

NumericFilenameGenerator

public NumericFilenameGenerator(java.util.regex.Pattern filenamePattern,
                                java.lang.String firstName,
                                char padChar,
                                int keyLen,
                                java.lang.String postFix)
Construct with the given params.

Parameters:
filenamePattern - The pattern to recognize generated filenames, where group 1 identifies the (unpadded) key (generated) portion of the filename.
firstName - The name of the first file to generate in the directory (including its postFix).
padChar - The character to prepend to the generated portion of a local name to keep names of length keyLen.
keyLen - The total/constant length of generated keys with padding.
postFix - The filename postFix to attach after a generated key (i.e. ".html.gz")
